TASK_TEAM=0
TASK_DESCRIPTION=Doey Expert found this during 425. Go writers and shell readers use different status file formats; Go-format files silently dropped by shell readers. Either standardize on one format or make readers accept both. Low risk, high payoff for status DB reliability.
TASK_SUBTASKS=1:W2.1: Standardize status file format on 'STATUS: BUSY' (colon+space). Update Go ctl.WriteStatus and any other Go writers under tui/cmd/doey-ctl/ to write the colon+space format. Verify all shell readers in .claude/hooks/ and shell/ work. Run tests/test-bash-compat.sh.:done
